  "text": "where F x denotes the set of the followers of legislator x. The Kulczynski dissimilarity is recommended as an alternative to the commonly used Jaccard measure when the size of F x exhibits a wide range as in our Twitter data (Fig 4) [CITATION_1] . The dissimilarity between legislators i and j in the roll call data is, similarly,",
